              status="closed"
            >
              <span slot="content">I know this will be sacrilegious to say, but I think I actually enjoyed this more than Blue. I can admit that Blue is the better film -- more artful, more stylistically unique, with a stronger lead performance -- but the story here was more interesting, had a bit of mystery.

Watching these dysfunctional, strangely codependent people navigate each other in a weirdly manipulative way held my attention. There’s something off about their entangled dynamic and it gives the film a kind of strange, quirky energy.

Dramatically, it&#39;s also less on the nose than Blue. Where Blue addresses independence, or being alone, this is a somewhat satirical take on equality. Or inequality, rather. And the thematic elements of this power struggle are clear, but a bit more indirect.</span>
